-- Pick one channel attribution per customer (most recent)
WITH source AS (
    SELECT
        customer_id,
        channel,
        attributed_at,
        ROW_NUMBER() OVER (
            PARTITION BY customer_id
            ORDER BY attributed_at DESC
        ) AS row_num
    FROM {{ ref('stg_customer_channels') }}
)
SELECT
    customer_id,
    channel
FROM source
WHERE row_num = 1

-- int_transactions_enriched.sql
```sql
-- Enrich transactions with customer and store data
WITH source AS (
    SELECT
        t.transaction_id,
        t.customer_id,
        t.store_id,
        t.amount,
        t.transaction_date,
        COALESCE(c.channel, '(unknown)') AS channel,
        COALESCE(s.city, '(unknown)') AS city
    FROM {{ ref('stg_transactions') }} t
    LEFT JOIN {{ ref('int_deduped_customer_channels') }} c
        ON c.customer_id = t.customer_id
    LEFT JOIN {{ ref('stg_stores') }} s
        ON s.store_id = t.store_id
)
SELECT
    transaction_id,
    customer_id,
    store_id,
    amount,
    transaction_date,
    channel,
    city
FROM source
```
